ActImmigration and Refugee Protection Act
SubjectRegulations Amending the Immigration and Refugee Protection Regulations
PrecisRegulations Amending the IMMIGRATION AND REFUGEE PROTECTION REGULATIONS in order to support the Government of Canada’s ability to collect immigration information from and disclose immigration information to the United States of America pursuant to the Agreement, and the Asylum Annex, while balancing the privacy interests of individuals whose information is shared with the need to maintain the integrity of Canada’s immigration program and the safety and security of Canada.
